        <event type="researchStep">
          <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en">Data processing: Create a 3D model of the site using
            the acquired images</head>
          <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en"><p>This step is related to the surveyed object and
              to the software used for processing the data. Usually it is possible to refer to a
              traditional photogrammetric workflow: <list>
                <item>Data loading</item>
                <item>Tie points extraction (Sparse point cloud)</item>
                <item>Camera Calibration</item>
                <item>Relative orientation</item>
                <item>Absolute orientation (using georef. data)</item>
                <item>Densification (Dense point cloud)</item>
                <item>Meshing (Triangulated mesh)</item>
                <item>Texturing</item>
                <item>DSM generation</item>
                <item>3D model exporting</item>
              </list>
            </p>
            <p>Software to use: <list>
                <item>Photogrammetric suite (MicMac, AgiSoft Metashape, Pix4D Mapper, etc.)</item>
              </list></p>
          </desc>
